msgctxt "80_Saki-chan"
msgid "So now it's all over, hm?"
msgstr "...Así que todo ha terminado."

msgctxt "92_Tanimura"
msgid "It is."
msgstr "...Así es."

msgctxt "104_Tanimura"
msgid "My dad mentioned something cryptic at the very end of his notebook. It was about taking care of the treasure that K left behind..."
msgstr "Mi padre escribió algo críptico al final de su cuaderno. Hablaba de cuidar el tesoro que K dejó atrás..."

msgctxt "116_Saki-chan"
msgid "So he did..."
msgstr "Al final sí lo hizo..."

msgctxt "128_Tanimura"
msgid "Saki-chan, you told me that if I kept looking into this case, I'd find out things about my past."
msgstr "Saki-chan, me dijiste que si seguía investigando este caso, descubriría cosas sobre mi pasado."

msgctxt "140_Saki-chan"
msgid "I guess you already know by now."
msgstr "Supongo que ya lo sabes."

msgctxt "152_Tanimura"
msgid "Yeah. My real dad was Kaga."
msgstr "Sí. Mi verdadero padre era Kaga."

msgctxt "164_Saki-chan"
msgid "...Yes."
msgstr "... Sí."

msgctxt "176_Saki-chan"
msgid "Now it's true that Kaga-san let himself get corrupted by money... but he hoped you would never lose your sense of justice like he did."
msgstr "Kaga-san se dejó cegar por el dinero, pero siempre deseó que tú jamás dejaras atrás el sentido de justicia que él perdió."

msgctxt "188_Saki-chan"
msgid "That's why he named you Masayoshi. Because your name means justice."
msgstr "Por eso te llamó Masayoshi, porque tu nombre significa justicia."

msgctxt "200_Tanimura"
msgid "It all makes sense now."
msgstr "...Así que era por eso."

msgctxt "212_Saki-chan"
msgid "I hope you're not too shocked by the truth."
msgstr "Espero que la verdad no te haya impactado demasiado."

msgctxt "224_Tanimura"
msgid "Like I told you before, I really don't care who my real dad is."
msgstr "Ya te lo dije antes, en verdad me da igual quién sea mi verdadero padre."

msgctxt "236_Saki-chan"
msgid "How can you still say that?"
msgstr "¿Por qué dices eso?"

msgctxt "248_Tanimura"
msgid "I grew up reading this notebook ever since I was a little boy."
msgstr "Desde que era un niño, crecí leyendo este cuaderno."

msgctxt "260_Tanimura"
msgid "It was the closest connection I've had to any sort of parents, real or not."
msgstr "Para alguien como yo, que creció sin padres, este diario era lo único que me hacía sentir su presencia."

msgctxt "272_Saki-chan"
msgid "Because it has the words of both your real father and your foster father."
msgstr "Porque contiene las palabras tanto de tu padre biológico como de tu padre adoptivo."

msgctxt "284_Tanimura"
msgid "Right. It tells the story of two brave men who gave their\\r\n"
"lives to fight against a giant crime syndicate..."
msgstr "Así es. Cuenta la historia de dos hombres valientes que dieron\\r\n"
"sus vidas luchando contra un enorme sindicato del crimen..."

msgctxt "356_Tanimura"
msgid "Well, I guess I'll see you around."
msgstr "Bueno, ya te he molestado bastante."

msgctxt "368_Saki-chan"
msgid "Oh! Almost forgot."
msgstr "¡Oh! Casi lo olvido."

msgctxt "380_Tanimura"
msgid "Hmm?"
msgstr "¿Mmm?"

msgctxt "392_Saki-chan"
msgid "Hehe... Just wanted to give you a li'l token of my affection. Here. You. Go-oh! ♥"
msgstr "Je, je... solo quería darte una muestrita de mi cariño. Toma, es para ti. ♥"

msgctxt "428_Tanimura"
msgid "Ummm..."
msgstr "Emmm..."

msgctxt "440_Saki-chan"
msgid "Oh, come on! Don't make me say it!"
msgstr "¡Ay, tonto! ¡No me hagas decirlo!"

msgctxt "452_Saki-chan"
msgid "...Just don't be a stranger, okay?"
msgstr "...Pásate a verme de vez en cuando, ¿sí?"

msgctxt "464_Tanimura"
msgid "I won't. And... whenever you get the chance, maybe we could sit down together some time and you could share some stories with me... about my old man."
msgstr "Lo haré. Y... quizá podamos sentarnos juntos algún día y me podrías contar algunas historias sobre mi viejo..."

